:''[[Viroqua (spider)|Viroqua]]'' is also a genus of [[jumping spiders]].

'''Viroqua''' is a city in [[Vernon County, Wisconsin|Vernon County]], [[Wisconsin]], [[United States]]. The population was 4,335 at the 2000 census. The city is located within the [[Viroqua (town), Wisconsin|Town of Viroqua]].
== Notable people==
* [[Irwin Hendrick Dregne]] - World War II fighter ace and group commander
* [[Mark C. Lee]] - United States Astronaut
* [[Jeremiah McLain Rusk]] - Governor of Wisconsin, Secretary of Agriculture
* [[Butch Vig]] - Record producer and musician
* [http://www.af.mil/bios/bio.asp?bioID=7993 Dr. Richard Tubb] - Personal physician to President [[George W. Bush]]

==Geography==
[[Image:WIMap-doton-Viroqua.png|right|Location of Viroqua, Wisconsin]]Viroqua is located at {{coor dms|43|33|23|N|90|53|15|W|city}} (43.556534, -90.887663){{GR|1}}.

According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of 8.5 [[km<U+00B2>]] (3.3 [[square mile|mi<U+00B2>]]). None of the area is covered with water.

==Demographics==
As of the [[census]]{{GR|2}} of 2000, there were 4,335 people, 1,990 households, and 1,112 families residing in the city. The [[population density]] was 511.9/km<U+00B2> (1,327.3/mi<U+00B2>). There were 2,105 housing units at an average density of 248.5/km<U+00B2> (644.5/mi<U+00B2>). The racial makeup of the city was 98.73% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.07% [[African American (U.S. Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 0.16% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.46% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.18% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.39% from two or more races. 0.69% of the population were [[Hispanic]] or [[Latino]] of any race.

There were 1,990 households out of which 24.5% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 43.6% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.3% had a female householder with no husband present, and 44.1% were non-families. 39.5% of all households were made up of individuals and 22.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.10 and the average family size was 2.81.

In the city the population was spread out with 21.4% under the age of 18, 7.5% from 18 to 24, 23.3% from 25 to 44, 21.6% from 45 to 64, and 26.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 44 years. For every 100 females there were 82.7 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 77.8 males.

The median income for a household in the city was $28,804, and the median income for a family was $35,475. Males had a median income of $29,589 versus $20,046 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $17,172. About 9.8% of families and 12.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 16.8% of those under age 18 and 12.1% of those age 65 or over.

